==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Loafer
<hw>Loaf"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[G.
<ets>l⟦aum⟧ufer</ets> a runner, Prov. G. <ets>laufer</ets>,
<ets>lofer</ets>, fr. <ets>laufen</ets> to run. See
<er>Leap</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who loafs; a lazy
lounger.</def> <rj><au>Lowell.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A type of shoe without laces which can be easily
slipped on or off; -- originally a trademark; <as>as, he bought a new
pair of <ex>loafers</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>loafing</ent>⟦br⟧
